  "local_port": 47690,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How one can apply for IIMs after cat results?",
  "response": "Applying to Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) after CAT results involves a structured process. Here's a concise, organized guide:\n\n### **1. CAT Results and Cutoffs**  \n- **Check Results**: CAT scores and percentiles are released (typically in January).  \n- **Review Cutoffs**: Each IIM sets minimum CAT percentile cutoffs (varies by category). Check official IIM websites for specific cutoffs.\n\n### **2. Shortlisting by IIMs**  \n- **Initial Shortlist**: IIMs shortlist candidates based on CAT score, academics, work experience, and diversity.  \n- **Preferences Selected During CAT**: If you listed specific IIMs during CAT registration, they may automatically consider you.  \n- **New Applications**: Some newer IIMs (e.g., via the **Common Admission Process/CAP**) allow post-CAT applications. Check individual IIM portals for forms and deadlines.\n\n### **3. Application Process**  \n- **Detailed Application Form (DAF)**: Shortlisted candidates must submit a DAF with academic details, work experience, essays, and recommendations.  \n  - **Fees**: Pay application fees for each IIM.  \n  - **Deadlines**: Adhere to deadlines (usually January\u2013February).  \n\n### **4. Interviews and Assessments**  \n- **WAT-PI/GD**: Older IIMs (A, B, C) conduct Written Ability Tests (WAT), Group Discussions (GD), and Personal Interviews (PI).  \n- **CAP Interviews**: Newer IIMs often use a common interview pool.  \n- **Preparation**: Research current affairs, practice essays, and mock interviews.\n\n### **5. Final Admission Offer**  \n- **Composite Score**: IIMs evaluate CAT score, academics, work ex, diversity, and interview performance.  \n- **Offer Release**: Final offers are announced (April\u2013May). Acceptances may require a fee deposit.  \n- **Waitlist**: Some candidates may receive offers later if seats open.\n\n### **6. Key Considerations**  \n- **IIM-Specific Policies**: Each IIM has unique criteria; check their websites.  \n- **Programs**: Apply to specific programs (e.g., PGP, PGP-FABM) as needed.  \n- **Diversity**: Non-engineering backgrounds or gender diversity may improve chances.\n\n### **7. Resources**  \n- **Official Websites**: Regularly visit [IIM Admission Portals](https://www.iimcat.ac.in) and individual IIM sites.  \n- **Forums**: Platforms like Pagalguy or CAT-related communities for peer insights.\n\n### **Timeline Summary**  \n- **January**: CAT results, shortlisting begins.  \n- **February\u2013March**: DAF submission, interviews.  \n- **April\u2013May**: Final offers.\n\nBy following these steps and staying proactive, candidates can navigate the post-CAT application process effectively.",
